<TITLE> JU teachers election Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jahangirnagar University (bdnews24.com)-Thirteen teachers will be elected to the university's syndicate, finance committee and academic council in Monday's election. Abu Bakar Siddique, the university's acting registrar, will oversee the voting, open from 9am to 2pm at the Teacher's Club. Around 456 teachers will vote in the polls. Election commissioner Siddique told bdnews24.com that all preparations had been complete. Incumbent vice-chancellor Sharif Enamul Kabir is heading the panel of ruling Awami League-backed teachers, while former VC Mustahidur Rahman is leading opposition BNP-supported teachers. Six teachers would be elected to the syndicate as per the 1973 University act. One representative would be elected from each of the dean, provost, professor, associate professor, assistant professor and lecturer categories. Six teachers would be elected as academic council members with three representatives from the associate professors' category and as many from assistant professors and lecturers' category. One teacher will be elected to the finance committee. bdn
